class Solution {
    public String breakPalindrome(String palindrome) {
        if (palindrome.length() == 1) return "";
        char[] chars = palindrome.toCharArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < chars.length / 2; i++) {
            if (chars[i] != 'a') {
                chars[i] = 'a';
                return new String(chars);
            }
        }
        chars[chars.length - 1] = 'b';
        return new String(chars);
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the first half of the palindrome string, replacing the first non-'a' character with 'a' to make the string not a palindrome while keeping it lexicographically smallest. If no such character exists, it replaces the last character with 'b' to achieve the same result. This approach ensures the solution is efficient and meets the constraints of the problem.

